'break main' + 'run' stops execution at the first line of main, before any code runs.
'next' steps one line forward. Keep stepping until you're past the 'int key = 0' line.
'print key' shows the current value. 'set variable key = 0x1337' overwrites it in memory.
'continue' (or 'c') resumes execution until the next breakpoint or the program exits.
